Prompt: In Northern Securities Co. v. United States (293 U.S. 193), what was the proposition deduced from Minnesota v. Northern Securities Co. (123 Fed. Rep. 692, 705)?
Response: The proposition deduced from Minnesota v. Northern Securities Co. (123 Fed. Rep. 692, 705) was that the formation of associations or corporations is not illegal, because the result will be to restrain competition.
